H0.text: What is the name of the circular temple built by Agrippa in Rome and dedicated to all the gods. Temple of Jupiter

H1.text: What is the name of the circular temple built by Agrippa in Rome and dedicated to all the gods. Pantheonium

H2.text: What is the name of the circular temple built by Agrippa in Rome and dedicated to all the gods. Agrippa's Dome

H3.text: What is the name of the circular temple built by Agrippa in Rome and dedicated to all the gods. PANTHEON

A4.text: The Pantheon was built on the site of an earlier temple, which had been commissioned by Marcus Vipsanius Agrippa during the reign of Augustus (27 BC–AD 14).

A5.text: The name 'Pantheon' is from the Ancient Greek 'Pantheion' (Πάνθειον) meaning 'of, relating to, or common to all the gods'.
